# CFX security best practices

- Always validate `source` on the server side; never trust client-sent data
- Never expose server-only logic to the client
- Use ACE permissions for admin commands: `RegisterCommand('adminCmd', handler, true)`
- Prefix server events intended only for internal use to prevent remote triggering
- Never store passwords, tokens, or API keys in resource files; use server convars
- Rate-limit expensive server events to prevent abuse
- Validate all parameters in server event handlers (type checks, range checks)
- Use `TriggerLatentClientEvent` for large data transfers to avoid network spikes
- Never use `ExecuteCommand` with user-provided input without sanitization
